Step 1: Compute the Debt to Asset Ratio.
• From the balance sheet we see that the only liabilities are the current liabilities (Accounts Payable + Taxes Payable), which total 5,515,978.61.
• Total Assets at end date is 21,662,106.19.
• Therefore, Debt to Asset Ratio = 5,515,978.61 / 21,662,106.19 ≈ 0.2546, which rounds to 0.25.

Step 2: Compute the Gross Profit Margin.
• From the income statement, Gross Profit is 300,421.65 and Total Revenue is 863,371.65.
• Gross Profit Margin = (300,421.65 / 863,371.65) ≈ 0.3480, or 34.80% when expressed as a percentage.

Step 3: Compute the Operating Cash Flow Ratio.
• From the cash flow statement, Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities is -2,419,019.09.
• Total Current Liabilities (from the balance sheet) is 5,515,978.61.
• Thus, Operating Cash Flow Ratio = (-2,419,019.09 / 5,515,978.61) ≈ -0.4386, which rounds to -0.44.

Finally, we present the solution in the required JSON format:

{
  "solution": {
    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.25", 
    "Gross Profit Margin": "34.80%", 
    "Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "-0.44"
  }
}
